-- Bouygues sees 10 bln eur synergies from SFR deal- Le Figaro
-- By Leila Abboud
-- Wed Mar 05, 2014 01:09PM EST
-- None



PARIS, March 5 (Reuters) - Bouygues <BOUY.PA> has promised to deliver 10 billion euros ($13.7 billion) worth of cost savings from its proposed combination with larger mobile telecoms rival Vivendi's <VIV.PA> SFR, according to a report in Le Figaro newspaper.

Bouygues' offer, which was expected to be submitted to Vivendi by 1900 GMT, would leave Vivendi will a 40 percent stake in the newly-created company, the paper said without citing sources. The company will not sell its stake in train and turbine maker Alstom <ALSO.PA> to finance the deal, the report said.